# Dependency Management Standards

## Adding Dependencies
- Check if similar functionality exists before adding new packages
- Prefer smaller, focused packages over large utility libraries
- Verify package health (downloads, last update, open issues)

## Version Pinning
- Use exact versions (`--save-exact`) for production dependencies
- Allow minor/patch updates for dev dependencies
- Document version upgrade reasons in PR

## Security Checks
- Run `npm audit` or `yarn audit` before committing lock files
- No dependencies with known critical vulnerabilities
- Prefer packages with active maintenance (updated in last 6 months)

## Forbidden Packages
- Deprecated packages
- Packages with unresolved security advisories
- Packages that bundle their own dependencies unnecessarily